title: Issah Moro
text:
Issah Moro (born December 24, 1974) is a <a href="Ghana">Ghana</a>ian retired <a href="Association%20football">football</a> forward.
During his career he played with Ghanaian clubs <a href="Great%20Olympics">Great Olympics</a> and Dwarfs, before moving to Slovenia where he played for <a href="NK%20Beltinci">Beltinci</a> and <a href="NK%20Olimpija%20Ljubljana%20%281945%29">Olimpija</a>. He then moved to Austria, where he played for <a href="First%20Vienna%20FC">First Vienna FC</a>, before returning to Slovenia, playing for <a href="NK%20Ivan%C4%8Dna%20Gorica">Livar</a>. He also played for <a href="KF%20Trep%C3%A7a%2789">KF Trepça'89</a> in the <a href="Football%20Superleague%20of%20Kosovo">Kosovar Superleague</a>.
